TENPINS TEMPEST lunged outwardly and spotted the leaders a pair of lengths at the start, trailed while saving ground, yet failed to factor. KATIE'S C pressed two wide and between horses into the turn, but yielded at the five sixteenths pole, and tired. MO DIXIE DIVA was restless in the starting gate, then was pinched back while put to crowded quarters passing the nine sixteenths pole, chased from off of the pace in the three path, and was outrun turning for home.
